00005 /*
00006  * This structure contains raw lines for Two Line Elements (TLEs)
00007  * and also the decoded values. Here is how the TLEs are formated;
00008  *
00009  *  Line 0:
00010  *      Columns     Example                         Description
00011  *      -------     -----------         ----------------------------------------------------------
00012  *      1-24        ISS (ZARYA)         The common name for the object based on information from 
00013                                         the SatCat. 
00014  *
00015  *  Line 1:
00016  *      Columns     Example                         Description
00017  *      -------     -----------         ----------------------------------------------------------
00018  *      1           1                   Line Number
00019  *      3-7         25544               Object Identification Number Search by object ID
00020  *      8           U                   Elset Classification
00021  *      10-17       98067A              International Designator Search by International Designator
00022  *      19-32       04236.56031392      Element Set Epoch (UTC)
00023  *      34-43       .00020137           1st Derivative of the Mean Motion with respect to Time
00024  *      45-52(46-53??)       12345-7             2nd Derivative of the Mean Motion with respect to Time 
00025  *                                      NOTE: decimal point assumed.  This type of format is to be 
00026  *                                      read as: 0.12345e-7
00027  *      54-61       16538-3             B* Drag Term
00028  *      63  0       Element             Set Type
00029  *      65-68       513                 Element Number
00030  *      69          5                   Checksum
00031  *
00032  *  Line 2:
00033  *      Columns     Example                         Description
00034  *      -------     -----------         ----------------------------------------------------------
00035  *      1           2                   Line Number
00036  *      3-7         25544               Object Identification Number
00037  *      9-16        51.6335             Orbit Inclination (degrees)
00038  *      18-25       344.7760            Right Ascension of Ascending Node (degrees)
00039  *      27-33       0007976             Eccentricity (decimal point assumed)
00040  *      35-42       126.2523            Argument of Perigee (degrees)
00041  *      44-51       325.9359            Mean Anomaly (degrees)
00042  *      53-63       15.70406856         Mean Motion (revolutions/day)
00043  *      64-68       32890               Revolution Number at Epoch
00044  *      69          3                   Checksum
00045  *
00046  */
00047 typedef struct _SgpTLE {
00048 
00049     // Raw lines
00050     char    Line0[80];  // Contains the common name for the object
00051     char    Line1[80];  // Contains identifiers derivatives of mean motion, drag term etc..
00052     char    Line2[80];  // Contains orbital elements (RA of Asc Node, mean anomaly, etc..)
00053 
00054 
00055     // Decoded Line0
00056     char    Name[80];           // Common object name
00057 
00058 
00059     // Decoded Line1
00060     int     IdNumber;           // Object identification number
00061     char    ElsetClass;         // Elset Classification
00062     char    IntDesig[20];       // International designator
00063     double  ElementSetEpoch;    // Element Set Epoch Time
00064     double  dMMdT1;             // 1st Derivative of the Mean Motion with respect to Time
00065     double  dMMdT2;             // 2nd Derivative of the Mean Motion with respect to Time
00066     double  BstarDrag;          // B* Drag Term
00067     int     ElementSetType;     // Element Set Type
00068     int     ElementSetNum;      // Element Set Number
00069     int     Line1CheckSum;      // Line1 Checksum
00070 
00071 
00072     // Decoded Line2
00073     double    Inclination;        // Orbit Inclination (degrees)
00074     double    RAofAscNode;        // Right Ascension of Ascending Node (degrees)
00075     double    Eccentricity;       // Eccentricity
00076     double    ArgOfPerigee;       // Argument of Perigee (degrees)
00077     double    MeanAnomaly;        // Mean Anomaly (degrees)
00078     double    MeanMotion;         // Mean Motion (revolutions/day)
00079     int       RevNumAtEpoch;      // Revolution Number at Epoch
00080     int       Line2CheckSum;      // Line2 Checksum
00081 
00082     // Extra (derived) stuff
00083     long int  Date;
00084     double    UT;
00085     int       Year;
00086     int       Month;
00087     int       Day;
00088     int       Doy;
00089     char      Dow[5];
00090     double    JD;             // Julian Date of Epoch
00091     double    Period;         // in minutes
00092     char      IntDesig2[20];  // e.g. 1989-046A
00093     char      ObjectType[20]; // SAT, R/B or DEB
00094     char      EpochStr[20];   // A more readabl version of the epoch time...
00095     double    YYYYDDDdFRAC;   // YYYYDDD.FRAC
00096     
00097 
00098 
00099 } _SgpTLE;
